Baltimore-area high school sports photos from October 2015. From Sun staff reports 
No. 9 Archbishop Spalding put 17 shots on goal to wear down host Severn in girls soccer Wednesday. 
Brooke Shehade dribbled to the 18-yard line and scored the winner midway through overtime as the Cavaliers (10-4-3, 5-1 Interscholastic Athletic Association of Maryland A Conference) won, 1-0, over the Admirals (5-11, 1-5). 
No. 3 Bel Air 5, Mount de Sales 2: Gabby Encarnacion made a game-high four goals to lead the Bobcats (12-0) past the host Sailors (5-9-1). 
Bel Air led 2-1 at the break. 
No. 13 Perry Hall 6, Franklin 0: Rachel Bohli scored twice to lead the Gators (10-4) past the host Indians (2-10). 
Boys 
No. 4 Calvert Hall 2, Mount Saint Joseph 1: Matt Breidenstein and Jeff Schaefer scored to lead the visiting Cardinals (10-4-1, 9-3-1 Maryland Interscholastic Athletic Association A Conference) past the Gaels (10-6, 7-5).
